cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SE

This paper discusses user tracking on the internet, which is a security and privacy concern. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves analyzing the configuration of web browsers and websites, which falls under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also presents a new attack technique, which could be categorized under cs.CY (Computers and Society). Finally, the paper involves evaluating the feasibility of tracking users, which could be categorized under cs.SE (Software Engineering).
